cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about a new approach for neural machine translation (NMT) using morphological and grammatical decomposition of words. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanism, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of linguistic information, which is related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of factors to handle larger vocabulary and reduce training time is also related to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the system on a specific dataset, which is related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
